# Fluff Date: 2026-02-28 16:10:19
<overview>
<p>The Hamilcar class DropShip is a unique space assault vessel developed by a Free Worlds League military think tank and manufactured by Irian Naval Systems. First entering service in 3054, this 3,600-ton aerodyne defies easy classification, combining BattleMech and aerospace fighter transport capability in a single hull optimized for zero-gravity assault operations. Initially dismissed by observers as a poorly conceived raider, the Hamilcar proved its worth as an integrated combat platform where the vessel, its embarked BattleMechs, and its fighter screen operate as a coordinated assault unit. Despite its innovative approach, the design remains a niche asset, dependent on its embarked forces to compensate for its own limited defensive capabilities.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>The post-Jihad refit of the Hamilcar reconfigures the bay layout to carry four BattleMechs, five battle armor squads, and two aerospace fighters, along with two small craft bays and 131 tons of cargo. The nose armament is substantially reworked: the Gauss rifle and ER large laser are retained, but the missile launchers are replaced with three Screen Launchers and five anti-missile systems for enhanced defensive capability against capital-grade threats. The wing armament retains the ER large lasers, ER PPCs, and Artemis-equipped LRM-20 and LRM-15 launchers, but replaces the large pulse lasers with large variable-speed pulse lasers for improved accuracy at varying ranges. The aft arc mounts an ER large laser, an Artemis-equipped LRM-15, and a Streak SRM-4. The expanded battle armor capacity and defensive systems reflect lessons learned during the Jihad about boarding actions and anti-missile warfare.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The post-Jihad refit variant reflects the evolving nature of space combat operations, incorporating battle armor transport and enhanced defensive systems developed in response to the Word of Blake's extensive use of capital-grade weapons. The variant serves in Republic-era naval formations where boarding operations and point-defense capability are prioritized over raw offensive firepower.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The Hamilcar was conceived by a Marik military think tank seeking a new approach to space assault operations. Manufactured at Irian Technologies, the design entered service in 3054 and was immediately met with skepticism. Many observers dismissed the vessel as an ill-conceived raider that was neither a proper fighter carrier nor a proper BattleMech transport. These criticisms overlooked the Hamilcar's true purpose as an integrated zero-gravity combat platform.</p><p>The design's reputation was transformed by a decisive engagement at the Concord system's L2 cargo station in late 3055, when terrorists seized the facility. A Hamilcar dispatched to the system demonstrated the design's intended doctrine flawlessly: launching its fighters as a screen while simultaneously deploying jump-capable BattleMechs against the station. The coordinated assault forced a rapid surrender and proved the viability of the Hamilcar's integrated combat concept. Despite this success, the design's limited fuel capacity, thin armor, and dependence on its fighter screen have kept production numbers modest, and the Hamilcar remains a specialized asset within the Free Worlds League Military's order of battle.</p>
</history>

